 from robert andrew ryan subject re monthly question about xcopyarea and expose events organization school of computer science carnegie mellon pittsburgh pa lines one nine nntp posting host po five andrew cmu edu in reply to excerpts from netnews comp windows x one nine apr nine three monthly question about xcop buzz moschetti bear com one zero five five a button widget when pressed will cause a new item to be drawn in the window this action clearly should not call xcopyarea or equiv directly instead it should register the existence of the new item in a memory structure and let the same expose event handler that handles regular expose events e g window manager driven exposures take care of rendering the new image hmmm clearly depends on your programming model it is not at all forbidden to draw outside the context of an expose event certainly any internal data structures should be maintained such that the visual appearance would be maintained properly whenever an expose event happens to be generated this doesn t preclude drawing immediately after updating the datastructures though rob